BACKGROUND: Feasibility of dignity therapy (DT) is well established in 
palliative care. Evidence of its efficacy, however, has been inconsistent and 
may stem from DT's primary effects differing from the outcomes measured in 
previous studies. We proposed that DT effects were in the spiritual domain and 
created a new outcome measure, Dignity Impact Scale (DIS), from items previously 
